The paper focuses on evaluating and proposing algorithms for salient object segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses dataset design bias and proposes a new dataset, which involves machine learning and data analysis (cs.AI, cs.LG). The proposed method for salient object segmentation involves using fixations, which is related to human-computer interaction and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper reports benchmark progress on existing datasets, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR).
